    "narrative": "Ghost Ride the WHIP enters today with a strong core anchored by **Vinnie Pasquantino** and **Mickey Moniak**, our top-scoring starts at 76.21 and 75.75, respectively. **Vinnie Pasquantino** benefits from a high-efficiency matchup against K. Montero, bolstered by an optimal 3-hole placement and a favorable park factor, while **Mickey Moniak** serves as our primary leverage play against the porous 7.36 xERA of Weiss. Both hitters possess massive dynamic platoon advantages, making them the engines for our daily R and RBI production. **Josh Naylor** also draws a premium assignment against Buehler; despite a neutral park, his 19% SP skill bonus and 4th-slot protection make him an essential play for our 5x5 categories.\n\nIn the hunt for our scarcest category, SB, **Brice Turang** (64.27) stands out as a critical start. His 86% success rate against the opposing pitcher, combined with an ideal lead-off/2-hole profile, creates a high-probability event for a swipe that his raw power-hitting peers cannot match. While **James Wood** (55.42) remains in the lineup despite a sub-60 score due to his elite sprint speed and top-of-the-order usage, he faces a stern test against Ashcraft, whose ability to hold runners to a 62% efficiency rate presents a legitimate risk to our stolen base strategy. **Jose Caballero** (63.52) earns a spot over alternatives because of his excellent platoon split against Suter, providing a necessary floor for an otherwise volatile middle-infield slot.\n\nOur most difficult decision involved balancing **Luis Campusano** (43.78) at catcher versus potential bench depth. While **Luis Campusano** barely clears the marginal threshold, he remains our preferred option as we preserve game caps, given that bench assets like **Gabriel Moreno** and **Max Muncy** are currently providing less upside in this specific slate. We are keeping a close watch on **Tyler Soderstrom**, who carries a strong 71.02 score despite a poor BvP history against Leiter; the park factor and platoon edge were simply too significant to ignore in favor of bench reserves like **Dalton Rushing** or **Zach McKinstry**. We are monitoring potential weather interference, but as of now, the aggressive deployment of our platoon-favored hitters remains the optimal path to maximizing our 5x5 totals.",
